# pi-remote

A pi extension that exposes a REST + WebSocket server so a phone (or any other
client) can drive the desktop pi session over the network. Pairs with the
[`pi-remote-android`](https://github.com/USER/pi-remote-android) mobile app.

## Commands

- `/remote start [host] [port]` - Start the server (default `127.0.0.1:8787`).
- `/remote start [host:port]` - Equivalent shorthand for the same endpoint.
  Use `0.0.0.0` if connecting from another machine on a tailnet.
- `/remote stop` - Stop the server.
- `/remote status` - Show running state.
- `/remote token` - Print the current auth token.
- `/remote token rotate` - Generate a new token.

## Protocol overview

The server speaks two surfaces:

- **REST** at `http://<host>:<port>/api/*` for one-shot commands and reads.
- **WebSocket** at `ws://<host>:<port>/ws` for streaming events.

All requests require `Authorization: Bearer <token>` (or the same token sent as
the first `{type:"auth"}` WS message). See [`protocol.ts`](./protocol.ts) for
the full message schema.

## Extension integration: remote UI requests

pi-remote acts as a **bridge** between extensions and connected mobile clients.
Any pi extension can ask for user input that simultaneously appears on the
desktop TUI and the mobile app, with a first-wins race.

### How it works

Extensions emit events on the global `pi.events` bus; pi-remote listens, forwards
requests to the WebSocket, accepts responses via REST, and re-emits replies on
the bus.

### Channels

| Channel | Direction | Payload |
|--|--|--|
| `remoteui:request` | extension → bridge | `{ requestId, kind: "select"\|"editor", title, message?, source, options?, allowMultiple?, allowFreeform?, allowComment?, prefill? }` |
| `remoteui:response` | bridge → extension | `{ requestId, payload, reason? }` |
| `remoteui:cancel` | extension → bridge | `{ requestId }` |
| `plan:toggle` | bridge → plan-mode | `undefined` (any subscriber that toggles plan-mode) |
| `plan:update` | plan-mode → bridge | `{ enabled?, progress? }` |

### Response semantics

- `payload === null` always means "no result". Use `reason` to disambiguate:
  - `"no_remote"` - no mobile client is currently connected. Caller should fall
    back to the desktop UI path.
  - `"cancelled"` - the user dismissed the dialog on the mobile side.
  - `"disconnected"` - the mobile client disconnected before responding.
- `payload` is `UISelectPayload` for `kind="select"`, `UIEditorPayload` for
  `kind="editor"`. See [`protocol.ts`](./protocol.ts).

### Recipe: race a desktop select against the mobile dialog

```ts
import { randomUUID } from "node:crypto";

async function racedSelect(pi: ExtensionAPI, ctx: ExtensionContext, title: string, choices: string[]) {
  const requestId = randomUUID();
  let settled = false;

  // Listen for response BEFORE emitting the request.
  const responsePromise = new Promise<any>((resolve) => {
    const off = pi.events.on("remoteui:response", (data: any) => {
      if (data?.requestId !== requestId || settled) return;
      settled = true;
      off();
      resolve(data);
    });
  });

  pi.events.emit("remoteui:request", {
    requestId,
    kind: "select",
    title,
    options: choices.map((c) => ({ title: c })),
    source: "my-extension",
  });

  // Race against the desktop TUI.
  const abort = new AbortController();
  const tuiPromise = ctx.ui.select(title, choices, { signal: abort.signal });

  const winner = await Promise.race([
    tuiPromise.then((v) => ({ origin: "tui", value: v })),
    responsePromise.then((env) => ({ origin: "remote", env })),
  ]);

  if (winner.origin === "tui") {
    pi.events.emit("remoteui:cancel", { requestId });
    return winner.value;
  } else {
    abort.abort();
    if (winner.env.payload === null) return undefined; // cancelled or no_remote
    return winner.env.payload.selections[0];
  }
}
```

### Recipe: editor that prefers mobile when available

Because `ctx.ui.editor` cannot be programmatically cancelled, the canonical
pattern is to send the request first and fall back to desktop only on
`reason === "no_remote"`:

```ts
async function racedEditor(pi: ExtensionAPI, ctx: ExtensionContext, title: string, prefill = "") {
  const requestId = randomUUID();
  const responsePromise = new Promise<any>((resolve) => {
    const off = pi.events.on("remoteui:response", (data: any) => {
      if (data?.requestId !== requestId) return;
      off();
      resolve(data);
    });
  });
  pi.events.emit("remoteui:request", { requestId, kind: "editor", title, prefill, source: "my-extension" });
  const env = await responsePromise;
  if (env.reason === "no_remote") return ctx.ui.editor(title, prefill);
  if (env.payload === null) return undefined;
  return (env.payload as { text: string }).text;
}
```

### plan-mode integration

The official plan-mode extension already wires itself up:

- On `session_start` it caches its `ExtensionContext` and emits an initial
  `plan:update`.
- It listens for `plan:toggle` and treats it as equivalent to running `/plan`.
- It emits `plan:update` whenever its enabled state or todo progress changes.

If you write an extension that wants to know plan state, listen to `plan:update`
rather than maintaining your own copy.

## Mobile client

The Android client is a Compose app that connects to one pi-remote endpoint at
a time. See the `pi-remote-android` repo for build instructions. The protocol
types mirror [`protocol.ts`](./protocol.ts) one-to-one in
`data/protocol/Models.kt` and `data/protocol/Events.kt`.

## REST endpoints

| Method | Path | Body | Purpose |
|--|--|--|--|
| GET | `/api/health` | - | Liveness; no auth required. |
| POST | `/api/auth/verify` | - | Verify the bearer token. |
| GET | `/api/state` | - | Current `RemoteState`. |
| GET | `/api/models` | - | Available models. |
| POST | `/api/model` | `{provider, id}` | Switch model. |
| POST | `/api/thinking-level` | `{level}` | Set thinking level. |
| POST | `/api/prompt` | `{text, delivery?}` | Send user message. |
| POST | `/api/abort` | - | Abort the current turn. |
| GET | `/api/sessions` | - | List sessions. |
| POST | `/api/sessions` | - | Create a new session. |
| POST | `/api/sessions/switch` | `{file}` | Switch active session. |
| GET | `/api/skills` | - | List installed skills. |
| GET | `/api/messages` | - | Replay session messages. |
| POST | `/api/ui/response` | `UIResponseBody` | Submit a remote UI dialog result. |
| POST | `/api/commands/plan` | - | Toggle plan-mode (503 if not installed). |

## Files

- `index.ts` - Extension entrypoint and event wiring.
- `server.ts` - HTTP + WebSocket server.
- `remote-ui-bridge.ts` - pi.events ↔ WS translation.
- `protocol.ts` - shared types.
- `state.ts` - `createRemoteState` helper.
- `auth.ts` - token persistence at `~/.pi/agent/extensions/pi-remote/.remote.local.json`.

import type { ThinkingLevel } from "@earendil-works/pi-agent-core";

export type DeliveryMode = "steer" | "followUp";

export interface RemoteModel {
	provider: string;
	id: string;
	name: string;
	reasoning: boolean;
	contextWindow: number;
	maxTokens: number;
}

export interface RemoteState {
	sessionId: string;
	sessionFile?: string;
	sessionName?: string;
	cwd: string;
	model?: RemoteModel;
	thinkingLevel: ThinkingLevel;
	/** Whether plan-mode extension is currently active. Driven by the bridge. */
	planMode: boolean;
	/** Backward-compatible placeholder for older remote clients. */
	webSearch: boolean;
	/** Pre-formatted progress string from plan-mode (e.g. "3/7 · current step"). */
	planProgress: string | null;
	isStreaming: boolean;
}

export interface RemoteSessionInfo {
	file: string;
	id: string;
	name?: string;
	cwd: string;
	createdAt: number;
	updatedAt: number;
	messageCount: number;
	firstMessage: string;
}

// --- Remote UI request protocol ---------------------------------------------
//
// Extensions emit `remoteui:request` on the pi.events bus and the bridge
// translates it to a WS event for connected mobile clients. The mobile client
// answers with POST /api/ui/response which the bridge re-emits as
// `remoteui:response` for the originating extension.

export interface UIOption {
	title: string;
	description?: string;
}

export type UIRequestKind = "select" | "editor";

export interface UIRequest {
	requestId: string;
	kind: UIRequestKind;
	title: string;
	/** Optional contextual message shown above options/editor. */
	message?: string;
	/** Source extension name, for client-side display only (e.g. "ask_user"). */
	source: string;
	/** Present when kind === "select". */
	options?: UIOption[];
	allowMultiple?: boolean;
	allowFreeform?: boolean;
	allowComment?: boolean;
	/** Present when kind === "editor". */
	prefill?: string;
}

/** Submitted by the mobile client. `status === "cancel"` means the user dismissed. */
export interface UIResponseBody {
	requestId: string;
	status: "submit" | "cancel";
	payload?: UISelectPayload | UIEditorPayload;
}

export interface UISelectPayload {
	kind: "select";
	selections: string[];
	freeformText?: string;
	comment?: string;
}

export interface UIEditorPayload {
	kind: "editor";
	text: string;
}

export type ClientEvent =
	| { type: "auth"; token: string }
	| { type: "prompt"; text: string; delivery?: DeliveryMode }
	| { type: "abort" }
	| { type: "set_model"; provider: string; id: string }
	| { type: "set_thinking_level"; level: ThinkingLevel }
	| { type: "set_settings"; planMode?: boolean; webSearch?: boolean }
	| { type: "ping" };

export type ServerEvent =
	| { type: "ready"; state: RemoteState }
	| { type: "state"; state: RemoteState }
	| { type: "assistant_delta"; text: string }
	| { type: "thinking_delta"; text: string }
	| { type: "tool_start"; toolCallId: string; toolName: string; input?: unknown }
	| { type: "tool_update"; toolCallId: string; toolName: string; text: string }
	| { type: "tool_end"; toolCallId: string; toolName: string; isError: boolean; output?: string }
	| { type: "agent_start" }
	| { type: "agent_end" }
	| { type: "queue_update"; steering: readonly string[]; followUp: readonly string[] }
	| { type: "ui_request"; request: UIRequest }
	| { type: "ui_cancel"; requestId: string }
	| { type: "error"; message: string }
	| { type: "pong" };

export function isThinkingLevel(value: unknown): value is ThinkingLevel {
	return value === "off" || value === "minimal" || value === "low" || value === "medium" || value === "high" || value === "xhigh";
}

export function isDeliveryMode(value: unknown): value is DeliveryMode {
	return value === "steer" || value === "followUp";
}

export function asRecord(value: unknown): Record<string, unknown> | undefined {
	if (!value || typeof value !== "object" || Array.isArray(value)) return undefined;
	return value as Record<string, unknown>;
}

package com.piremote.ui.connection

import androidx.lifecycle.ViewModel
import androidx.lifecycle.viewModelScope
import com.piremote.AppContainer
import com.piremote.data.ConnectionConfig
import com.piremote.data.PiRemoteClient
import com.piremote.data.RemoteApiException
import kotlinx.coroutines.flow.MutableStateFlow
import kotlinx.coroutines.flow.StateFlow
import kotlinx.coroutines.flow.asStateFlow
import kotlinx.coroutines.launch
import timber.log.Timber

data class ConnectionUiState(
    val host: String = "",
    val port: String = "8787",
    val token: String = "",
    val testing: Boolean = false,
    val errorMessage: String? = null,
    val infoMessage: String? = null,
)

class ConnectionViewModel : ViewModel() {
    private val tokenStore = AppContainer.tokenStore

    private val _state = MutableStateFlow(loadInitial())
    val state: StateFlow<ConnectionUiState> = _state.asStateFlow()

    private fun loadInitial(): ConnectionUiState {
        val saved = tokenStore.load()
        return if (saved != null) {
            ConnectionUiState(
                host = saved.host,
                port = saved.port.toString(),
                token = saved.token,
            )
        } else {
            ConnectionUiState()
        }
    }

    fun updateHost(v: String) { _state.value = _state.value.copy(host = v.trim(), errorMessage = null) }
    fun updatePort(v: String) { _state.value = _state.value.copy(port = v.trim(), errorMessage = null) }
    fun updateToken(v: String) { _state.value = _state.value.copy(token = v.trim(), errorMessage = null) }

    /**
     * Validate inputs, run /api/health then /api/auth/verify.
     * On success, persist config, build a [PiRemoteClient], and invoke [onConnected].
     */
    fun connect(onConnected: () -> Unit) {
        val current = _state.value
        val port = current.port.toIntOrNull()
        when {
            current.host.isBlank() -> _state.value = current.copy(errorMessage = "Host is required")
            port == null || port !in 1..65535 -> _state.value = current.copy(errorMessage = "Port must be 1-65535")
            current.token.isBlank() -> _state.value = current.copy(errorMessage = "Token is required")
            else -> {
                _state.value = current.copy(testing = true, errorMessage = null, infoMessage = null)
                val config = ConnectionConfig(host = current.host, port = port, token = current.token)
                viewModelScope.launch {
                    val tester = PiRemoteClient(config)
                    try {
                        val health = tester.health()
                        if (!health.ok) {
                            _state.value = _state.value.copy(testing = false, errorMessage = "Health check failed")
                            tester.shutdown()
                            return@launch
                        }
                        val authed = try {
                            tester.verifyAuth()
                        } catch (e: RemoteApiException) {
                            Timber.w(e, "verifyAuth failed")
                            false
                        }
                        if (!authed) {
                            _state.value = _state.value.copy(testing = false, errorMessage = "Token rejected by server")
                            tester.shutdown()
                            return@launch
                        }
                        tokenStore.save(config)
                        // Hand the same client to AppContainer so the chat screen reuses it.
                        AppContainer.setClient(tester)
                        _state.value = _state.value.copy(testing = false, infoMessage = "Connected")
                        onConnected()
                    } catch (e: Exception) {
                        Timber.w(e, "connect failed")
                        _state.value = _state.value.copy(
                            testing = false,
                            errorMessage = e.message ?: "Connection failed",
                        )
                        tester.shutdown()
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }

    fun forget() {
        tokenStore.clear()
        AppContainer.setClient(null)
        _state.value = ConnectionUiState()
    }
}

